<br>
&quot;Zeus. . .you have no idea who you are dealing with.&quot;<br>
<br>
She was still a bit mangled from her return from Illusia. She always had been beaten on the trip back up to Earth. She loved her time there, but being as she was at this time, she knew that her powers were weakened and she could not be much help to the village. . . but she would try with all her might.<br>
<br>
She stepped into the village with a smile. She saw all of the amazons preparing for the harsh weather. She sadly knew that some of them would not make it through. But she knew one thing. . .she would. As would Hippolyte.<br>
<br>
She opened her arms and a bright light came into her heart and straight into the ground below her feet. She felt a burning fire glow beneath her. As she fell to the ground when the light died, a small sprout shot up from below her. It them blasted up into a large tree. It blossomed and grew the fruits of Scynthia. A large fire went up around it, she placed her hands on the flames and they did not burn her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Amazons of Themiscrya, I have given you a great gift. No, I have given us a great gift. This tree will forever bear the fruit of the North. It will be a forever burning flame to help us through this time. Not even an Olympian can damamge it, for this came from our hearts and spirits. Zeus cannot kill that. And if our hearts die along with this winter. . . so goes the tree. Be brave my sisters .. &quot;<br>
<br>
She glanced at Hipp and Dawn.<br>
<br>
&quot;My friends. . . be brave and trust in our tribe.&quot;<br>
<br>
She then became weak and hit the ground to rest herself.<br>
